14) $u=x-y, v=x$ 라 놓으면 $J=\left|\begin{array}{cc}1 & -1 \\ 1 & 0\end{array}\right|=1$ 이고,
$R_{n}=\left\{(u, v) \in R^{2} \mid u^{2}+v^{2} \leq n\right\}$ 이다.
이 때, $R_{1}=\left\{(u, v) \in R^{2} \mid u^{2}+v^{2}<1\right\}$, $R_{2}=\left\{(u, v) \in R^{2} \mid 1 \leq u^{2}+v^{2}<2\right\}$,
$\cdots, R_{n-1}=\left\{(u, v) \in R^{2} \mid n-1 \leq u^{2}+v^{2}<n\right\}$ 이므로
$\lim _{n \rightarrow \infty} \iint_{D_{n}} e^{-\left[(x-y)^{2}+x^{2}\right]} d x d y=\lim _{n \rightarrow \infty} \iint_{R_{n}} e^{-\left[u^{2}+v^{2}\right]} d u d v$
$=\lim _{n \rightarrow \infty} \iint_{R_{1}} e^{-\left[u^{2}+v^{2}\right]} d u d v+\iint_{R_{2}} e^{-\left[u^{2}+v^{2}\right]} d u d v +\cdots+\iint_{R_{n-1}} e^{-\left[u^{2}+v^{2}\right]} d u d v$
$=\lim _{n \rightarrow \infty} \iint_{R_{1}} 1 d u d v+\iint_{R_{2}} e^{-1} d u d v+\cdots+\iint_{R_{n-1}} e^{-(n-1)} d u d v$
$=\lim _{n \rightarrow \infty} R_{1}$ 면적 $+e^{-1} \times R_{2}$ 면적 $+\cdots+e^{-(n-1)} \times R_{n-1}$ 면적
$=\pi+e^{-1} \pi+e^{-2} \pi+\cdots=\pi\left(1+e^{-1}+e^{-2}+\cdots\right)$
$=\pi \times \frac{1}{1-e^{-1}}=\frac{\pi e}{e-1}$
